# child-exit-zero-error-path.baseline
#
# Grandfathered list of child-side `_exit(0)` callsites whose
# surrounding context trips the heuristic in
# scripts/check-static/child-exit-zero-error-path.sh but which are in
# fact legitimate happy-path exits.
#
# Format: `path/to/file.c:lineno  reason text...`
# Lines starting with `#` and blank lines are ignored.  Whitespace
# between the key and the reason is collapsed.
#
# This baseline file should SHRINK over time, never grow.  When a
# callsite is hardened (changed to _exit(<sentinel>) or rewritten so
# the heuristic no longer fires), remove its line from this file.  A
# new `_exit(0)` reachable from a failure branch will FAIL `make
# check-static` rather than be silently added to this list.
#
# The bug class this file pins against: a child that bails on an
# error path with _exit(0) is invisible to reap_entry_is_fast_die()
# and contributes nothing to the fork-storm fast-die circuit breaker.
# See commit e9a9ae95a4b1 ("kcov: recovery exits with nonzero status
# so fast-die breaker fires") for the canonical fix shape.
